1
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:36,390
Did I kill them?

2
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:39,600
Hello?

3
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:57,200
[Blind Woman]

4
00:00:58,140 --> 00:01:00,970
[Episode 1: Forced Kiss]

5
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:02,960
Hello?

6
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:12,510
Mr. Zhong?

7
00:01:14,570 --> 00:01:15,210
Mrs. Zhong?

8
00:01:28,039 --> 00:01:28,630
Who's there?

9
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:36,680
Say something.

10
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:41,280
You can't see?

11
00:01:42,190 --> 00:01:42,830
Who are you?

12
00:01:45,440 --> 00:01:47,050
I'm the new temp hired by the Zhong family.

13
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:48,680
Who are you?

14
00:01:49,140 --> 00:01:49,780
Why are you here?

15
00:01:50,430 --> 00:01:51,400
I'm Lin Wanyue,

16
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:53,880
the piano tuner hired by Mrs. Zhong.

17
00:01:54,570 --> 00:01:56,280
She said her piano at home is out of tune

18
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,870
and asked me to come over to tune it.

19
00:01:58,570 --> 00:02:00,240
Mrs. Zhong and the others went out for something.

20
00:02:03,010 --> 00:02:03,680
I see.

21
00:02:05,050 --> 00:02:05,930
Then I'll come another day.

22
00:02:06,590 --> 00:02:07,030
Wait.

23
00:02:11,350 --> 00:02:12,960
Mrs. Zhong instructed me before she left.

24
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:15,110
She said that if someone came to tune the piano,

25
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:16,800
they should finish before leaving.

26
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:19,150
Moreover,

27
00:02:20,860 --> 00:02:22,220
it's not easy for you to come all the way here.

28
00:02:23,030 --> 00:02:23,710
Alright then.

29
00:02:30,570 --> 00:02:31,180
Sir.

30
00:02:31,820 --> 00:02:33,700
Could you tell me where the piano is?

31
00:02:45,270 --> 00:02:47,430
It's on your right, about six meters away.

32
00:02:49,579 --> 00:02:50,140
Okay.

33
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:16,350
Sir?

34
00:03:19,010 --> 00:03:19,570
What's wrong?

35
00:03:35,030 --> 00:03:36,300
Why did you direct me

36
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,400
in the wrong direction?

37
00:03:53,990 --> 00:03:55,360
Didn't you say that you couldn't see?

38
00:03:59,010 --> 00:04:00,120
I can't,

39
00:04:00,530 --> 00:04:01,900
but I can hear.

40
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,290
There's a very clear

41
00:04:03,450 --> 00:04:05,240
ticking sound coming from a clock in this direction.

42
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:07,230
If the piano is placed there,

43
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:08,630
it will create a strong resonance.

44
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,400
Mrs. Zhong has been learning the piano for so many years.

45
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,180
She wouldn't make such a stupid mistake.

46
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:16,010
Sorry.

47
00:04:16,870 --> 00:04:17,920
I sometimes mix up left and right.

48
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:19,750
The piano

49
00:04:20,279 --> 00:04:21,670
is actually on your left just now.

50
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,520
I know you're teasing me.

51
00:04:29,660 --> 00:04:30,220
It's okay.

52
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,120
So scary.

53
00:05:11,670 --> 00:05:12,310
What did you say?

54
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:16,150
The pitch of the piano is so scary.

55
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:19,480
How long does it usually take to tune?

56
00:05:20,740 --> 00:05:21,780
About two hours.

57
00:05:22,930 --> 00:05:23,960
This person's background is unclear.

58
00:05:25,620 --> 00:05:27,250
And her timing was too coincidental.

59
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,230
It's better to test her out again.

60
00:05:33,270 --> 00:05:34,700
[Jiangcheng Hospital]

61
00:06:05,670 --> 00:06:06,510
Miss Lin,

62
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:07,850
you've worked hard.

63
00:06:08,490 --> 00:06:09,200
Have some water.

64
00:06:18,690 --> 00:06:19,570
Thank you, sir.

65
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:28,660
I smell something strange.

66
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:30,170
Where?

67
00:06:30,980 --> 00:06:31,620
What smell?

68
00:06:35,990 --> 00:06:36,659
Blood.

69
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:49,580
I accidentally cut my hand

70
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:50,760
while working just now.

71
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,480
You should be more careful then.

72
00:07:06,530 --> 00:07:07,210
Sir,

73
00:07:07,330 --> 00:07:08,720
could you please close the window?

74
00:07:09,370 --> 00:07:11,380
I've been weak since I was young, so I can't stand the wind.

75
00:07:11,810 --> 00:07:13,250
This cursed weather...

76
00:07:15,010 --> 00:07:16,970
Okay. I'll close it right away.

77
00:07:58,250 --> 00:07:59,570
If you blink,

78
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:01,570
I'll kill you right away.

79
00:08:24,010 --> 00:08:25,420
Maybe I'm overthinking this.

80
00:08:29,130 --> 00:08:29,980
Thank you, sir.

81
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:41,960
It's tuned.

82
00:08:42,110 --> 00:08:43,990
Please tell Mrs. Zhong.

83
00:08:44,890 --> 00:08:46,090
Wasn't it supposed to take two hours?

84
00:08:47,850 --> 00:08:48,660
That's how long it takes others.

85
00:08:50,380 --> 00:08:51,090
I'll take my leave then.

86
00:08:51,660 --> 00:08:53,020
Okay, I'll see you out.

87
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:54,860
Thank you.

88
00:09:12,690 --> 00:09:13,450
Why did you stop?

89
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:22,760
I've been sitting for too long.

90
00:09:22,940 --> 00:09:24,090
My legs are a bit uncomfortable.

91
00:09:25,370 --> 00:09:26,300
I'll go open the door for you.

92
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:53,040
Thank you. I'll be on my way now.

93
00:10:15,540 --> 00:10:16,730
It was really a bloodstain.

94
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:18,940
The bloodstain

95
00:10:19,230 --> 00:10:20,950
carries traces of cigar smoke and perfume.

96
00:10:21,620 --> 00:10:22,380
You can't see?

97
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:24,090
Mrs. Zhong and the others went out for something.

98
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:27,400
It seems Mr. and Mrs. Zhong have already been murdered.

99
00:10:30,070 --> 00:10:32,400
Sorry. I sometimes mix up left and right.

100
00:10:32,910 --> 00:10:34,120
I accidentally cut my hand

101
00:10:34,420 --> 00:10:35,420
while working just now.

102
00:10:35,610 --> 00:10:37,380
No, he didn't cut his hand.

103
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:38,320
He killed someone!

104
00:10:39,210 --> 00:10:40,900
No, I have to report this to the police.

105
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:41,850
Report to the police?

106
00:10:49,980 --> 00:10:51,490
So, you knew I'd killed them?

107
00:10:52,070 --> 00:10:52,830
Shouldn't you...

108
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:55,970
Shouldn't I be inside the door...

109
00:10:59,100 --> 00:10:59,730
right?

110
00:11:02,260 --> 00:11:03,640
Over there! Freeze!

111
00:11:03,660 --> 00:11:04,210
Help!

112
00:11:05,020 --> 00:11:05,690
Freeze!

113
00:11:05,850 --> 00:11:06,640
Stop right there!

114
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,680
If you dare to make a sound,

115
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:13,030
I'll kill you right away.

116
00:11:30,660 --> 00:11:31,140
Watch out!

